    <content_encoded><![CDATA[I always go through a period of intense anxiety and depression upon finishing a big book project—the bigger the book, the more intense the emotional fallout. It's hard to work on a project for years, night-and-day for the last few months, and then, boom, it's off to the printer and we have nothing to show for all our work. The month it's being printed is a long, tough month. So, in an effort to make this month go by a little faster, I've decided to let the secret out: after seven years, the true sequel to <a href="/books/days.html"><em>Days of War, Nights of Love</em></a> is only a month away. It's our most ambitious book yet, and we've put everything we have into it. <a href="/books/er.html">The teaser page is here</a>, and we'll update it with details (like, um, the title) a bit at a time over the coming month. Also, issue #5 of <a href="/rt/">Rolling Thunder</a> should be available right before the end of the year; sorry for the delay—we've had our hands full.]]></content_encoded>
